<div class="panel panel-primary">
    <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#fellapp-instructions-auto">
                Instructions for Auto-Installing Google Scripts
            </a>
        </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="fellapp-instructions-auto" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
            <p>
                1) Open command console
            </p>
            <p>
                2) Go to the local ORDER folder 'order-lab\utils\google-integration\'
            </p>
            <p>
                3) Run 'python fellappsimple.py --title MyScript', where 'MyScript' is a prefix for the
                Fellowship Application and Recommendation Letter scripts.<br>
                For example, if the name is 'MyScript', the local copies of the Fellowship Application script
                will be installed in order-lab\utils\google-integration\scripts\MyScriptFellApp and the script
                name on Google will be MyScriptFellApp, and the local copies of the Recommendation Letter
                script will be installed in order-lab\utils\google-integration\scripts\MyScriptRecLet
                and the script name on Google will be MyScriptRecLet.
            </p>
            <p>
                4) Open https://script.google.com/home and open google scripts 'MyScriptFellApp' and 'MyScriptRecLet'.<br>
                Set the permission as described in the bottom of the section 1.1 in the "Instruction for Google Sites Integration":
                ‘Deploy’ -> ‘Manage deployments’ -> click edit icon -> click ‘Deploy’ on the bottom ->
                click ‘Authorize access’ -> choose account -> click ‘Allow’
            </p>

        </div> <!-- panel-body -->
    </div> <!-- panel-collapse -->
</div> <!-- panel panel-primary -->

